> **Version:** v1.1.0  
> This page documents behavior guaranteed in TealTiger v1.1.0.


# Decision Model

## Why Decisions?

TealTiger returns a stable, typed **Decision** object from policy-enforcing components so application code can handle outcomes predictably.

## Decision fields (contract)

- `action`: ALLOW | DENY | REDACT | TRANSFORM | REQUIRE_APPROVAL | DEGRADE
- `reason_codes`: stable identifiers explaining the outcome
- `risk_score`: 0â€“100
- `mode`: ENFORCE | MONITOR | REPORT_ONLY
- `policy_id`, `policy_version`
- `correlation_id` (required), `trace_id` (optional)

## Handling pattern

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  A[Decision.action] -->|ALLOW| B[Proceed]
  A -->|DENY| C[Block + error]
  A -->|REQUIRE_APPROVAL| D[Human approval]
  A -->|REDACT/TRANSFORM| E[Apply change]
  A -->|DEGRADE| F[Fallback / downgrade]
```

## Example (pseudo)

```ts
// switch(decision.action) { ... }
```

## Best practices

- Treat `reason_codes` as machine-readable constants for analytics and tests.
- Use `risk_score` for routing and escalation.
